    In [8]:
    d=
ef age_cat(age):
   =20
    if age >=3D 0 and age < 10:
        return '0-10'
    if age >=3D 10 and age < 20:
        return '10-20'
    if age >=3D 20 and age < 30:
        return '20-30'
    if age >=3D 30 and age < 40:
        return '30-40'
    if age >=3D 40 and age < 50:
        return '40-50'
    if age >=3D 50 and age < 60:
        return '50-60'
    if age >=3D 60 and age < 70:
        return '60-70'
    if age >=3D 70 and age < 80:
        return '70-80'
    if age >=3D 80 and age < 120:
        return '80+'

titanic['Age_cat']=3Dtitanic.Ag=
e.apply(lambda x: age_cat=
(x))
titanic=3Dtitanic.dropna<=
span class=3D"p">()
titanic=3Dtitanic.sort_values('Age')
